fundamentals.description:

This clause specifies the information requirements for the exchange of
     		configuration-controlled design of parts, assemblies, interconnects, interfaces, networks, and templates.
     		This clause specifies the information requirements for the exchange of
     		configuration-controlled definition of requirements for those items.
     		These items, including requirements, are considered to be products in this part of ISO 10303.



The management of the configuration of those products is addressed in this part of ISO 10303,
     		and is concerned with authorizations and the associated approvals given by persons in organizations.
     		The structured list of materials, components, templates, or other data items needed to make a product can be exchanged,
     		along with initial product design requirements as well as requirements for revised part versions.
     		Directive for work to proceed on these initial or modified product versions is addressed in this part of ISO 10303.



     		This part of ISO 10303 addresses exchange and sharing of information about the planned usage of products in a product model,
     		and also includes data about the different products that are sold by an organization to its customers
     		enabling an organization to control the configuration of these products.
     		This part of ISO 10303 provides the structure through which a product, unique versions of a product,
     		and different design discipline views of a product can be defined.
     		Several predefined views of a product that are specific to the electronics/electrotechnical industry are provided.
     		The details of these views and other relevant information is organized in conformance options.
     		An overview of the available conformance options is given here.


