4.1.2.8 Interconnect design



As in the assembly design there is an interface definition, known as a usage view, which provides the support
required to isolate the CAD model for the interconnect from that for the assembly while maintaining full traceability through the hierarchy.  The connections supported by the interconnect are included in the usage view to support trade studies and test.
Further, the usage view includes various options for physical shape  models to support analysis.  Embedded passive and active components are supported, as is various non traditional materials such as optical fiber for interconnect.
Microwave models (where features of the design are considered to be components) are supported, as is the abstraction that a terminal of a component in the interconnect is on the edge of the component model rather than the surface.
Full traceability of the physical netlist to the as layed out geometry is provided for planar, three dimensional and manifold surface layouts.
Full support is provided for treatment of the mechanical aspects of the interconnect, including materials, stackup, and Geometric Dimensioning and Tolerancing.


     		Manifold surface models may be used for molded and composite structures.





